>Out of the top of my head the only thing that makes &#x27;\0&#x27; terminated strings special in C is that it&#x27;s the way string literals are represented. It would be trivial to recode all of string.h using addr + len instead of nul terminated.<p>exactly, anywhere you would have
    if(str[i] == NULL) 
you replace with 
    if (str.s + i == str.end)
